George Okoh In Makurdi A former Governor of Benue State, Samuel Ortom, is presently being interrogated by the operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) at the anti-graft’s office in Makurdi. The former governor, who drove into the premises of the EFCC in his SUV, located along Godo Aluor Street, Old GRA, Makurdi arrived around 10am. He was later joined by his two former aides –former Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Terver Akase and Principal Special Assistant, Abraham Kwaghgu. As at the time of filing this report, Ortom was still with the EFCC officials. Details later…